  "$comment": "Immunity & hazard-removal SOURCE map. Each effect/hazard maps to a source-predicate; the generic immuneTo / canRemove atoms look the effect up here and evaluate the source-predicate against the member. Add a new immunity by editing data — no schema change. Source-predicate grammar (a node is matched if it holds for the member): {\"type\": name|[names]} member is (one of) that type; {\"ability\": [ids]} ability in list; {\"item\": [ids]} item in list; {\"move\": [ids]} knows one of; {\"grounded\": true}; {\"weather\": name} requires active weather; {\"all\": [..]} = AND; {\"anyOf\": [..]} = OR (also the top-level form); {\"typeImmuneToMove\": true} member's typing is immune to the incoming move's type (used by per-move moveTag immunities like ohko: Flying vs Fissure).",
